JOHANNESBURG - History was made last week when Asia's largest MMA promotion, One Championship, held two massive events just a week apart with Hero's Dream in Yangon and Legends of the World in Manila. The greatest sporting hero in the history of Myanmar, Aung La N Sang faced the Cameroonian behemoth, Alain Ngalani in the first event before Featherweight Champ Martin 'The Situ-Asian' Nguyen moved up to Lightweight to challenge Eduard 'Landslilde' Folayang for the latters' golden buckle in the second. So grab a seat for some of the best combat action highlights of the week!